body:
The latest master (dbb69412e56ebd66e3a88a0589c5f061db496269) Verilates the following code without an error.
```systemverilog
module t();
   import "DPI-C" function void f(int i[3]);
   int i[3];
   initial f(i);
endmodule
```

But C++ compiler complains as below.
```
In file included from Vt__ALL.cpp:3:
./Vt.cpp:73:15: error: assigning to 'int' from incompatible type 'IData *' (aka 'unsigned int *')
    i__Vcvt = i;
              ^
1 error generated.
```



Looking at the Verilated code, I suspect non-open unpacked array is not supported yet. 
```c++
VL_INLINE_OPT void Vt::__Vdpiimwrap_t__DOT__f_TOP(IData/*31:0*/ i[3]) {
    VL_DEBUG_IF(VL_DBG_MSGF("+    Vt::__Vdpiimwrap_t__DOT__f_TOP\n"); );
    // Body
    int i__Vcvt;  // <= Temporary variable is scalar, not an array
    i__Vcvt = i;
    f(i__Vcvt);
}
```

I am going to implement this feature.
Please let me know if I misunderstand the standard or overlook the ongoing work.
